org.sbml.jsbml

Class SBMLReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.SBMLReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable

    public class SBMLReader
extends Object
implements Cloneable, Serializable
    Provides methods for reading SBML from files, text strings or streams.

    This SBMLReader is just a wrapper for the actual implementation in SBMLReader.

    This class is provided for compatibility with libSBML and to avoid problems if the internal of jsbml change, so it is preferable to use it instead of directly using SBMLReader.

    The SBMLReader class provides the main interface for reading SBML content from files and strings. The methods for reading SBML all return an SBMLDocument object representing the results.

    In the case of failures (such as if the SBML contains errors), the errors will be recorded with the SBMLErrorLog object kept in the SBMLDocument returned by SBMLReader. Consequently, immediately after calling a method on SBMLReader, callers should always check for errors and warnings using the methods for this purpose provided by SBMLDocument.

    • Field Detail

      • UNKNOWN_XML_NODE

        public static String UNKNOWN_XML_NODE
        String used when reading an SBML file, to store XMLNode as user object when the XMLNode does not represents something known from the 'core'. What SBML core know is Notes, Annotation and the Constraint message that are all encoded as XMLNode.

      • readSBML

        public SBMLDocument readSBML(File file)
                      throws XMLStreamException,
                             IOException
        Reads an SBML document from a File.

        This method is identical to readSBMLFromFile(String filename) or readSBML(String filename).

        If the File named file does not exist or its content is not valid SBML, one Exception will be thrown.

        This methods is not part of the libSBML SBMLReader API.

        Parameters:
        file - the file to be read.

        Returns:
        an SBMLDocument created from the SBML content.
        Throws:
        XMLStreamException - if any other problems prevent to create a SBMLDocument
        IOException - if the file does not exist or cannot be read.
